  "id": "019d2964-bc2b-7ad0-9d43-6b2a2f1f45ee",
  "content": "# GPU Monitoring + Inference Health Probes — Design Decisions (2026-03-26)\n\nCloses chunzhe10/corvia#5 and chunzhe10/corvia#6 in a single PR.\n\n## Architecture Decision: Inference-Owned Probes\n\nThe inference server owns all health/metrics state. corvia-server is a thin consumer that reads via gRPC Health() RPC. Rationale: single source of truth, no duplicate probe logic, inference can self-diagnose drift without external polling.\n\n## Key Design Choices\n\n1. **Canary triggers on first LoadModel, not server boot** — models load on-demand via gRPC, so the canary can't run until an embedding model exists. Before first load, Health() returns probe_status: \"pending\".\n\n2. **Microsecond precision for probe times** — baseline_us/last_probe_us (u64) instead of milliseconds. Prevents division-by-zero on fast hardware. Guard: if baseline_us == 0, drift_pct = 0.0.\n\n3. **CSV over XML for nvidia-smi** — `--query-gpu` CSV with power.draw/power.limit fields (~50ms) instead of `-q -x` XML (~200-500ms). Separate `--query-compute-apps` call for process list only.\n\n4. **3s timeout on nvidia-smi, 2s on intel_gpu_top** — SIGKILL on expiry. Prevents thread pool exhaustion when GPU driver hangs.\n\n5. **Cache stampede protection** — `refreshing: bool` flag in GpuMetricsCache. Concurrent requests get stale data instead of each spawning nvidia-smi.\n\n6. **intel_gpu_top graceful degradation** — check binary existence first, kill after first JSON frame, fall back to sysfs-only on ENOENT/EPERM/timeout. No feature flag needed.\n\n7. **EP name normalization** — short names (\"cuda\", \"openvino\", \"cpu\") matching existing BackendKind::Display, not ORT-internal names.\n\n8. **Configurable drift threshold** — health_probe_drift_threshold_pct (default 100) in [inference] config, alongside health_probe_interval_secs (default 60).\n\n9. **serde(skip_serializing_if) on all new Option fields** — backward compatible JSON: new fields absent when None, not serialized as null.\n\n10. **InferenceProbeStatus as Rust enum** — with serde(rename_all = \"lowercase\") instead of raw String. Values: pending, healthy, degraded, failed, unreachable.\n\n## Spec Location\n\nrepos/corvia/docs/rfcs/2026-03-26-gpu-monitoring-inference-health-design.md",
